[{"question":"You\u0027re not implacably opposed to running for president?","answer":"No, I\u0027m not.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":9,"aSentId":10},{"question":"Could America be ready for another Bush in the White House?","answer":"I mean, look, this is a time to serve.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":12,"aSentId":13},{"question":"And what did you think of last night?","answer":"Well, I didn\u0027t see it because I was flying out to San Francisco, but this morning, bright and early, I saw what other people thought of the debate.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":21,"aSentId":22},{"question":"I mean he\u0027s -- he\u0027s consistent, isn\u0027t he?","answer":"He\u0027s very consistent.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":30,"aSentId":31},{"question":"Are you prepared to do this?","answer":"Well, I don\u0027t have as much weight behind me as Chris Christie, but I\u0027m getting up there.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":37,"aSentId":38},{"question":"What should America be doing -- what should American politicians be doing?","answer":"I think I have a sense of history, for starters.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":73,"aSentId":74},{"question":"You support their right to protest?","answer":"Oh, yes, absolutely.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":90,"aSentId":91},{"question":"So we should blame your brother, basically?","answer":"Well, we do that all the time, but not in this particular case.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":105,"aSentId":106},{"question":"Do you feel confident that enough is being done to prevent that?","answer":"You know, I think -- I think our banks are stronger today than they were in September of 2008, and they\u0027re certainly stronger in terms of their capital ratios compared to the European banks.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":122,"aSentId":123},{"question":"Do you think it\u0027s kind of anti the culture of the country?","answer":"It feels -- when you travel to Asia, particularly, you know, you get this spirit of optimism that\u0027s quite remarkable, and also a feeling that they look at us and kind of say, you know, poor older brother, you know, your days are behind you.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":128,"aSentId":129},{"question":"Why has education always been your great passion?","answer":"Well, I think I learned it at my mama\u0027s knee to start with.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":153,"aSentId":154},{"question":"Quite frightening, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"It\u0027s very frightening.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":163,"aSentId":164},{"question":"Why has nobody really got to grits with this?","answer":"Look, I think -- I think our country has rested on its laurels.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":178,"aSentId":179},{"question":"And how much should be driven from the state?","answer":"Well, today, it\u0027s anywhere from 8 to 10 percent.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":198,"aSentId":199},{"question":"What do you think is the optimum?","answer":"Where it is today is fine in terms of the relevance of education.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":202,"aSentId":203},{"question":"What are the key, simple ways that other states, and therefore America, collectively, can get to grips with this corrosive education system?","answer":"A focus on early childhood literacy, so the children come prepared to learn.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":212,"aSentId":213},{"question":"Do even teachers\u0027 unions get this, do you think, or is this still, again, a very old-fashioned sense of what a union should be doing?","answer":"This is like one of those fights in the previous segment, I believe, that we\u0027re -- that it\u0027s the transition from kind of the old \u002770s way of doing things to the 21st century way of doing things.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":229,"aSentId":230},{"question":"What\u0027s the trick to being successful in Florida, if you\u0027re a Republican candidate right now?","answer":"Well, Florida\u0027s an incredible -- it\u0027s purple, it\u0027s very purple.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":252,"aSentId":253},{"question":"What\u0027s it like having a brother and a dad who have both been president of the United States?","answer":"It\u0027s different.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":267,"aSentId":268},{"question":"Do you have to have that ability to cope with huge pressure, but also have the family, the balance?","answer":"Absolutely.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":283,"aSentId":284},{"question":"Well, that\u0027s an extraordinary thing to witness, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"And we didn\u0027t talk about it.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":291,"aSentId":292},{"question":"What was the toughest things for you to do?","answer":"I would say in the second term, the turning against him because of the war was difficult.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":307,"aSentId":308},{"question":"Was that the right thing to do?","answer":"No.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":310,"aSentId":311},{"question":"Does he miss being president?","answer":"I\u0027m sure he misses the White House, misses the service.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":336,"aSentId":337},{"question":"Why not personally?","answer":"Well, because it\u0027s personal.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":388,"aSentId":389},{"question":"ORGAN: Can you see yourself running in the future?","answer":"I can --","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":403,"aSentId":404},{"question":"Isn\u0027t it like a calling for you Bushes now?","answer":"No, it isn\u0027t.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":405,"aSentId":406},{"question":"Could you see the situation where the personal reasons, which I won\u0027t press you on -- but where those would go away enough for you to consider running perhaps in 2016?","answer":"That\u0027s pure -- that\u0027s just hypothetical, so I can\u0027t answer.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":418,"aSentId":419},{"question":"You\u0027re not implacably opposed to running for president?","answer":"No, I\u0027m not.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":420,"aSentId":421},{"question":"You don\u0027t just imagine one day just walking into the Oval Office?","answer":"Let\u0027s move to digital learn.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":425,"aSentId":426},{"question":"Is this a scoop?","answer":"This is a scoop.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":451,"aSentId":452},{"question":"Some of this, Governor Bush, does modern technology help kids learn better and faster than the old-fashioned technology?","answer":"I believe that passionately.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":456,"aSentId":457},{"question":"What is your view about competition, whether it\u0027s sporting or academic, in schools in America?","answer":"I think --","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":470,"aSentId":471},{"question":"Are you in favor of egg and spoon races?","answer":"I am.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":472,"aSentId":473},{"question":"What do you think, Governor Bush?","answer":"I think he\u0027s wrong.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":505,"aSentId":506},{"question":"Governor Wise?","answer":"I happen to think -- I agree with Warren Buffett on the taxes.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":519,"aSentId":520},{"question":"Do you know how many people you both executed?","answer":"I think during eight years, I\u0027ve probably -- I\u0027m going to be off a little bit, probably 50 people.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":534,"aSentId":535},{"question":"If you had the decision, if you were the president of the United States, would you try now and stop the death penalty?","answer":"No.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":550,"aSentId":551},{"question":"How are you going to link it to education?","answer":"ISE: Because DNA is modern technology.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":562,"aSentId":563},{"question":"Let me ask you first, Governor Bush?","answer":"Consistently higher graduation rates.","docId":"111012pmt","qSentId":568,"aSentId":569}]